    Research

    FSV UK fully supports the socio-scientific research. The Faculty integrates and co-ordinates the research plan it has acquired with several departments of  the Faculty of Arts, Charles University. Within this framework, FSV UK has made a commitment to provide the professional public with a critical and scientifically-based reflection on the development of Czech society from a long-term perspective.

International Staff Week

International Staff Week

International Staff Week is a five-day event organised by the International Office of the Faculty of Social Sciences, Charles university, which includes seminars, workshops, presentations and active participation of experts from the home university and international partners. In addition, the designed programme with a focus on the processes of internationalization of the university includes social and cultural activities. The event is offered to the faculty's partner universities.

International Staff Week 2023

Mental health and wellbeing issues on university campuses are on the rise. There is a strong and expanding evidence base indicating that university students are a ‘very high risk population’ for psychological distress and mental disorders. Given that a substantial proportion of students will experience mental health difficulties during their time at university, how can universities ensure they provide supportive and ‘health-promoting’ environments? And how can universities provide a supportive services for its academic and administrative staff? Join our staff week and share your experience and practice from your university.

What?

The theme for International Staff Week 2023 will be "Mental health and wellbeing of students and staff". During the five day programme, participants will be able to network, share experiences as well as get new perspectives and ideas for their work. We welcome participants from universities with rich portfolio of services and activities in well-being to give presentations and share best practice with other colleagues. 

When?

International Staff Week is organised annually in spring. The next Staff Week will be organised from 12th to 16th June 2023 in Prague, Czech republic.

Why?

Chance to network and share best practices with professionals from Charles university and our partner universities.

Discussions about important topic that HEIs need to address currently.

Experience Czech culture.

Completing your Erasmus+ Staff Exchange.

For whom?

The programme is designed for staff members of Faculty of Social Siences‘ partner universities. We welcome colleagues from departments such as International Office, Student wellbeing services, Study services, Human resources, Communications, marketing and alumni services, Career and recruitment services, Research, development and innovation services etc.

How to apply?

You can send your applications by filling this google form: https://forms.gle/TLq5TF3Mj8pNbxBN9

Application deadline: 31st March 2023

See the preliminary programme here.

Contact information: svoz@fsv.cuni.cz
